-- Manufacturing CEOs to attend White House meeting
-- 
-- Tue Dec 15, 2009 8:56pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/12/16/us-manufacturing-whitehouse-idUSTRE5BF06Q20091216

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Top chief executives from the U.S. manufacturing sector will attend a meeting hosted by Vice President Joe Biden in Washington on Wednesday, a White House spokesman said on Tuesday. 

 Leaders from Dow Corning Corp DOWCR.UL, Procter & Gamble ( PG.N ), Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co GT.N and others will attend the meeting about the future of the manufacturing sector, the spokesman said. "The Vice President will discuss this Administration's commitment to a strong manufacturing sector as a vital part of both the American economy and the rebuilding of the American middle class," the White House said in a statement. Other leaders attending the meeting include Secretary of Commerce Gary Locke, Secretary of Labor Hilda Solis, and Lawrence Summers, director of the White House National Economic Council. Here is a list of the CEOs expected to attend, according to the White House: Stephanie Burns of Dow Corning Keith Wandell of Harley-Davidson Inc ( HOG.N ) Jeff Turner of Spirit Aerosystems Holdings Inc ( SPR.N ) Robert McDonald of Procter & Gamble David Cote of Honeywell International Inc ( HON.N ) Robert Keegan of Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co Daniel DiMicco of Nucor Corp ( NUE.N ) John Faraci of International Paper Co ( IP.N ) Ronald Hall of Bridgewater Interiors James McGregor of McGregor Metalworking Dan Janka of MAG Scott Welsh of Mohawk Electrical Systems (Reporting by  Jeff Mason ; Editing by  Peter Cooney )